		<div class="comment_text"><p>Yay for rewatching it!  I never really got all the Wesley hate either.  Yes, he was eager and at times naive, but he was also a teenager.  Some people remarked that he was too "goodie" but considering the entire culture of humanity at that point, I'd have been more surprised and disappointed if he'd acted like a "typical" teen today. :-)</p><p>I liked Troi okay myself, though I wish the whole Imazadi thing with Riker had been explored more versus being a quick connection in the first episode then a random plot device later.  The two Imazadi books by Peter David are great reads for that side of it (also helps round out Troi's character more).  My favorite episode with her though was the one where she lost her powers and had to live without the edge of knowing how everyone else feels (i.e. normal) :-D</p><p>DS9 is indeed very Cardassian rich, so if you wanted to know more about them, it shouldn't be too disappointing.  Bajor, the Maquis, and those fun Ferengi also feature quite a bit. :-)</p><p>Are you planning to watch Voyager the same as well?</p></div>
