		posted on 5/12/2014 at 5:39 PM
		</div>
		<div class="comment_text"><p>I wouldn't mind doing a complete re-watch myself, though I've seen all of the episodes multiple times already. Right on about John Delancie as Q. FYI, Chris Hardwick recently did a GREAT interview with him on Nerdist, and it's interesting to hear more about him personally, outside of that character. He's a genuinely interesting guy, and he also helped get a documentary about Bronies made! His relationship with the entire "My Little Pony" fandom is hilarious.</p><p>"Inner Light" always stands out to me as the greatest single episode. Really strong writing in that one, and oddly enough it was kind of low-key with the space action. Other huge favorites for me were "Yesterday's Enterprise" and "Cause and Effect". I can't help but laugh a bit when Kelsey Grammer pops onto the viewscreen at the end.</p><p>FWIW, I really thought they made a great effort with the final episode, too. Similar to what Vince Gilligan did with "Breaking Bad", there was a lot of fan service, making a real effort to give loyal viewer and long-time Trek fans what they wanted. Lots of action, lots of those "what happens after Picard is no longer Captain" type moments. The time jumping was a little belabored at points, but I think they pulled it off. I was in the Army at the time, and remember watching it together with a bunch of fellow soldiers who were fans. We all digged it.</p></div>
